extends ../partials/layout-docs

//- Override default config variables
append config
  - var pageTitle = 'Components'
  - var isNestedFile = true
  - var breadcrumbs = [{'title': 'Home', 'link': '../index.html'}, {'title': 'Docs', 'link': '#'}]

//- Page Content
block content
  .pb-5.mb-2
    .alert.alert-info.alert-with-icon.font-size-sm.mb-4(role='alert')
      .alert-icon-box
        i(data-feather='info').alert-icon
      | <strong>Component</strong> - is a snippet of HTML code with assosiated CSS classes and sometimes attached JavaScript functionality that is rendered by the browser as a standalone website element. They can be mixed together to produce more complex components.
    p Along with all Bootstrap 4 components MStore introduces new elements you can use across website. More than 40 components in total.
    p: a(href='../components/alerts.html' class='font-weight-semibold' target='_blank') List of all Components as well as their visual reference and code snippets can be found here.
    p.pb-3: a(href='https://getbootstrap.com/docs/4.3/components/alerts/' class='font-weight-semibold' target='_blank') Bootstrap 4 Components and documentation.
    p.pb-1: strong Below is the image showing how to see code snippet for each component:
    img(src='../img/docs/component.png' alt='Component Show Code').d-block.img-thumbnail
